<br>
1. Each player may give up to 100pp to their newbie character for equipment and spells. But no twinking!<br>
<br>
2. Have a blast.<br>
<br>
If you have any ideas, suggestions, additional rules, or would like to go along with this please reply. <br>
<br>
Additional ideas:<br>
Use any character that is untwinked to lvl 9 so that way there is no exp loss possible. Lvl 9 gives most hybrids their spells and some casters their pets. Could make things more interesting. <br>
<br>
Guild names:<br>
1. Blue Team<br>
2. Red Team<br>
Just for the spirit of things<br>
<br>
<br>
I will be taking everyones ideas that I recieve over the next couple of weeks and compile a set of guidelines, I will also be looking for someone to run the second team. Both team leaders will be out of the competition because they will have to coordinate together to insure that all rules are upheald, although I dont see many rules except for the twinking issue. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ipkusthegnome>IpkusTheGnome</A> at: 5/21/03 4:21:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nerissagoldenrose>NerissaGoldenrose</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nxane.com/nerissa/purpleNotes10x10.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#8E9173>(5/21/03 2:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsguildwars.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.nxane.com/nerissa/yellowRose1b.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Am I crazy?</span><hr size=1> That sounds like fun, if you can get the guilds created beforehand, which I think still requires 10 members on separate accounts and getting through the petition queue.  It could be just for a day, or an all-weekend event, with team (guild) leaders  sitting somewhere safe to tag new players.  Team leaders should be off-limits, since they would need to be essentially stationary, and should be bound wherever they will be sitting in case they die anyway.<br>
<br>
You'd have to decide if you were going to recruit each team, giving the team leaders equal chance at any player who showed up, or make some effort to coordinate between the leaders to maintain somewhat equal teams.  Maybe &quot;good&quot; races vs &quot;evil&quot; races?<br>
<br>
Anyone found to have twinked their character beyond the pre-set limits would need to be /guildremoved by his/her team leader, so you would need people in those positions you could trust not to look the other way at rule infractions in the name of their team &quot;winning&quot;. <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br><br>
